)Disclaimer! I am a Ps4 player and have been playing for months.) This game is AMAZING, its a beautiful step into the gacha part of video games, and this game is absolutely beautiful, from the story line to the amazing graphic designs, but, there are many things that i feel must be discussed. Primogems. Primogems are a reward and common to get, but i wouldnt say their easy to get, you get them during events, from chests, in mail, and more, but these gems will mean A LOT more than they seem. Which comes up to the next thing, wishing. You need primogems to wish and this where a HUMONGOUS PROBLEM erupts with players in this game. There have been many banners with characters to wish for, and if your a desperate player with no primogems, you start to get more and more desperate for primos the shorter the time for a character, leading them to buy, buy, buy away, using their money to buy primogems just for a character they love, which can lead to much more than you would think. 

To the devs: this is an amazing game, and i have nothing to complain about, and im sure you‚Äôve got this a lot, but i feel that if you added more generosity for primos and mora the experience would be better :) 
-Atlas

i feel like this game has its pros and cons; it‚Äôs not perfect ofc but it isnt the worse either! especially their business moves, etc.

pros;

VISUALS are absolutely gorgeous, character designs, the graphic qualities and the regions 10/10

lore!! as a new player there‚Äôs plenty of content (definitely recommend slowing down once and awhile take your time it‚Äôs not going anywhere!) out there to eat. especially simce everything is so new.

characters! each are their own individual they have their good side and their flaws. they seem so real, and not fake. i can relate to some of the characters or feel empathy towards them

cons;

not enough to do in the later games; what i mean is that in the emd game there‚Äôs nothing much to do but help farm comm abyss events. it‚Äôs just so repetitive, and as a genshin player we get burnout. leading us to stop play for weeks or months.

event rewards;
there‚Äôs not a lot of them, i believe the lanternrite only gave us around 680 primogems (dont take my word for it!). it is barely enough to do a 10 roll. it‚Äôs a major issue since there‚Äôs not a lot to do to get primogems especially for end game players. unless you buy them yourself.
